WEBVTT

00:02.268 --> 00:05.396
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>Theorizing that one could time travel</i>
<i>within his own lifetime,</i>

00:05.471 --> 00:09.169
<i>Dr. Sam Beckett stepped</i>
<i>into the Quantum Leap accelerator...</i>

00:09.242 --> 00:11.176
<i>and vanished.</i>

00:15.782 --> 00:18.376
<i>He awoke to find himself</i>
<i>trapped in the past,</i>

00:18.451 --> 00:22.046
<i>facing mirror images</i>
<i>that were not his own...</i>

00:22.122 --> 00:26.252
<i>and driven by an unknown force</i>
<i>to change history for the better.</i>

00:27.427 --> 00:31.363
<i>His only guide on this journey is Al,</i>
<i>an observer from his own time,</i>

00:31.431 --> 00:36.027
<i>who appears in the form of a hologram</i>
<i>that only Sam can see and hear.</i>

00:37.137 --> 00:41.437
<i>And so, Dr. Beckett finds himself</i>
<i>leaping from life to life,</i>

00:41.508 --> 00:44.602
<i>striving to put right</i>
<i>what once went wrong...</i>

00:44.677 --> 00:47.510
<i>and hoping each time</i>
<i>that his next leap...</i>

00:47.580 --> 00:49.810
<i>will be the leap home.</i>

00:51.351 --> 00:53.319
<i>[ Wind Whistling ]</i>

00:53.386 --> 00:56.321
[ Meows ]
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>That's the last of it.</i>

00:56.389 --> 00:59.051
Comin' through.

00:59.125 --> 01:01.889
Thanks. Thanks a million.
I don't want to hang you up anymore.

01:01.961 --> 01:04.724
I just didn't know
how I was gonna do it alone.

01:04.798 --> 01:06.823
It's hideous, isn't it?
[ Chuckles ]

01:06.900 --> 01:09.300
I know it's silly, but I'd just die
if anything happened to it.

01:09.369 --> 01:11.462
It's... all I got left from my dad.

01:11.538 --> 01:14.405
Then you sure don't want to
leave it behind for a hurricane.

01:14.474 --> 01:16.999
Hurricane?
[ Screeches ]

01:17.077 --> 01:19.272
Oh, boy.

