Yeah.

05:20.053 --> 05:22.851
<i>[ Barking ]</i>

05:24.424 --> 05:27.052
Harrison to 28. Come on in, Arch.
I know you're out there.

05:27.126 --> 05:30.527
<i>Quit foolin'. Arch, put your clothes on</i>
<i>and get out the backseat. 1 0-4?</i>

05:30.596 --> 05:32.928
[ Laughs ]
I swear!

05:34.000 --> 05:37.561
Yeah, 28... here.

05:37.637 --> 05:43.598
<i>Twenty-eight,you got a 1 0-22</i>
<i>to 3-0-5-sixer on U.S. 90. 1 0-4?</i>

05:43.676 --> 05:46.577
Uh- 1 0-22, huh?

05:46.646 --> 05:50.446
<i>Arch, haul butt over</i>
<i>to the Gulf View Apartments on 90...</i>

05:50.516 --> 05:52.450
<i>and make sure</i>
<i>everybody's outta there.</i>

05:52.518 --> 05:55.078
<i>Manager said</i>
<i>some of the people won't go.</i>

05:55.154 --> 06:00.319
<i>And after that, swing over to Unabelle's.</i>
<i>Make sure everything's goin'okay. 1 0-4?</i>

06:00.393 --> 06:03.328
Okay. Uh, this is Arch.

06:03.396 --> 06:06.297
Twenty-eight... out.

06:08.568 --> 06:11.628
<i>[ Sam Narrating ]</i>
<i>Growing up in Indiana,</i>
<i>I had seen plenty of tornadoes,</i>

06:11.704 --> 06:14.138
<i>but none of them</i>
<i>had prepared me for a hurricane,</i>

06:14.207 --> 06:17.643
<i>and they certainly didn't prepare me</i>
<i>for the terror of driving through one.</i>

06:17.710 --> 06:19.940
<i>I just hoped that if</i>
<i>I stayed on Highway 90,</i>

06:20.012 --> 06:23.072
<i>I could get to the apartments</i>
<i>before the hurricane did.</i>

06:23.149 --> 06:28.985
<i>* [ Pop ]</i>
<i>[ Man ] Uh,y'all go away.</i>
<i>We don't want any.</i>

06:29.055 --> 06:30.989
Mr.-
Hello there, " Occifer.''

06:31.057 --> 06:32.991
Lejeune? Uh-

06:33.059 --> 06:38.087
Uh, Mr. Lejeune, I'm Cissy Davis
of the Red Cross. This is Deputy Necaise.

06:38.164 --> 06:41.793
We've come to warn you
that this whole area is being evacuated,

06:41.868 --> 06:45.634
and you and everybody here are-
[ Chuckling ]

06:45.705 --> 06:47.639
are gonna have to leave.

06:47.707 --> 06:51.108
Oh, hell's bells.
The steaks ain't even done yet.

06:51.177 --> 06:53.441
You can't have a barbecue
without some steaks!

06:53.513 --> 06:55.606
There's a hurricane comin', folks.

06:55.681 --> 06:58.411
Yeah, and don't that play damnation
with the charcoal.

06:58.484 --> 07:01.146
I had to give up the Weber
and start grillin' 'em indoors.

07:01.220 --> 07:04.451
Well, you're gonna be grillin'
'em under water
if you don't leave here soon.

07:12.231 --> 07:14.028
Man. Strange.

07:14.100 --> 07:18.264
Depending on which eye I use,
you look different.

07:18.337 --> 07:20.271
Brown hair, black hair.

07:20.339 --> 07:23.467
Brown hair, black hair.
Brown, black, brown, black.
[ Sputters ]

07:23.543 --> 07:25.636
Pretty weird.

07:25.711 --> 07:29.738
<i>Makes you seem</i>
<i>almost like two different people.</i>
<i>Now ain't that somethin'?</i>

07:29.816 --> 07:33.377
Yeah, well- I don't know
what you're talkin' about,
but you all have to get out of here now.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.251
[ Laughs ]
Son, let me tell you.

07:36.322 --> 07:41.316
About two years ago,
this place went co-op.
Y'all know what that means?

07:41.394 --> 07:45.694
- <i>I don't know. Uh,you gettin'</i>
<i>ready to sell for a profit ?</i>
- [ Laughs ]

07:45.765 --> 07:49.895
Hell, no. I'm gonna wait
three years before I do that.

07:49.969 --> 07:55.464
What it does mean, though,
is that this deluxe, three bedroom,

07:55.541 --> 07:59.500
two bath,
shag carpeted piece of heaven-

07:59.579 --> 08:03.208
[ Chuckles ]
is private property.

08:03.282 --> 08:06.843
<i>I own it.</i>
<i>You can't make me go.</i>

08:06.919 --> 08:10.685
But a hurricane can and will
if you stay here.

08:10.756 --> 08:13.190
I been through a lot worse
hurricanes than this.

08:13.259 --> 08:15.727
It's all just
a bunch of rain and wind.

08:15.795 --> 08:19.231
So thank you kindly,
but, uh, we gonna be just fine.

08:19.298 --> 08:24.930
Now if you'll excuse me,
I got a hurricane party to attend to.

08:25.004 --> 08:27.404
[ Chuckling ]
Whoo!

08:30.343 --> 08:32.903
I guess it's on to Unabelle's.
Yeah.

08:32.979 --> 08:36.573
<i>[ Sam Narrating ]</i>
<i>Driving along the coast to Unabelle's,</i>

08:36.649 --> 08:40.779
<i>it was easy to see why people</i>
<i>needed to be evacuated.</i>

08:40.852 --> 08:44.289
<i>With each passing minute,</i>
<i>the hurricane drew closer and closer,</i>

08:44.357 --> 08:50.318
<i>and it seemed like nature herself</i>
<i>was punishing the land</i>
<i>for some unknown transgression.</i>

08:50.396 --> 08:53.194
<i>I just hoped that I wasn't</i>
<i>going to be punished with it.</i>

08:56.802 --> 09:00.636
You know, in a way I can't blame him
for not wantin' to leave.

09:00.706 --> 09:06.110
I mean- Most of your life,
nothin' every happens.

09:06.178 --> 09:10.478
Now, we're livin' on the edge.
Literally.

09:10.550 --> 09:14.646
God, can't you feel it?

09:14.720 --> 09:18.212
<i>The-The power, the possibilities.</i>

09:18.291 --> 09:21.920
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, I don't know, I-

09:21.994 --> 09:26.124
Ever since I was a little kid,
I-I always felt so charged up...

09:26.198 --> 09:29.656
whenever there was
a thunderstorm or somethin'.

09:29.735 --> 09:32.932
I just feel... more alive.

09:34.140 --> 09:37.667
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>Able to leap tall buildings</i>
<i>in a single bound?</i>

09:37.743 --> 09:40.075
Yeah.

09:40.146 --> 09:44.173
Move mountains, right wrongs,

09:44.250 --> 09:46.514
travel through time,

09:48.220 --> 09:50.415
grow 1 0 feet tall and run forever.

09:52.425 --> 09:55.087
Yes.

09:55.161 --> 09:57.129
[ Mouthing Words ]

09:59.265 --> 10:01.495
We better get inside.

10:03.502 --> 10:06.835
<i>[ Radio, Indistinct ]</i>

10:08.507 --> 10:10.873
Cissy? And Archie!

10:10.943 --> 10:14.106
You both here
to join us for the ride?
If you'll have us.

10:14.180 --> 10:17.377
That's the good thing
about being a designated shelter-

10:17.450 --> 10:21.409
lets you catch up with folks
you haven't seen for a while.
Yes!

10:21.487 --> 10:24.217
Cissy, you can help me
fill the tubs with water.
Okay.

10:24.290 --> 10:29.057
And, Arch, fill this
and finish pumping those lanterns,
would you, please?

10:29.128 --> 10:31.756
Yes, ma'am.
Well-

10:32.765 --> 10:35.063
Duty calls.
[ Chuckles ]

10:35.134 --> 10:39.036
<i>[ Radio Continues ]</i>
Later.

10:45.444 --> 10:47.878
Oh. Hi, Sam.
What's the matter?

10:47.947 --> 10:49.881
Huh?
What's wrong?

10:49.949 --> 10:52.144
Nothin'. I was just
goin' for a walk and-
What happened?

10:52.218 --> 10:54.152
Oh, I had a fight with Tina.

10:54.220 --> 10:59.248
Oh.
I can never figure out
when life is so short...

10:59.325 --> 11:02.226
how we always find time to argue.

11:02.294 --> 11:06.162
You'd think that we would look
at the good things around us.

11:07.800 --> 11:11.531
Carpe diem.
Seize the day.

11:11.604 --> 11:14.767
[ Together]
And that's the way it should be.

11:17.076 --> 11:20.375
But we don't seem
to remember those things.

11:20.446 --> 11:23.677
Speaking of which-
Oh, uh, yeah.

11:23.749 --> 11:28.584
[ Beeping ]
It's, uh, August 1 7, 1 969,
and you're in-

11:28.654 --> 11:31.179
Jackson's Point, Mississippi.
Jackson- Okay.

11:31.257 --> 11:35.023
Your name is... Archie Necaise.

11:35.094 --> 11:38.188
You're a deputy sheriff,
and, uh, according to Ziggy,

11:38.264 --> 11:41.597
there's a 96.2 <i>%-</i>

11:42.802 --> 11:44.793
six point-
Al.

11:44.870 --> 11:48.397
two percent, uh,
chance that you're here...

11:48.474 --> 11:52.877
to save a nurse named... Cissy Davis
from getting killed by Camille.

11:55.815 --> 11:59.216
Who's-Who's Camille?
No, it's no " who.'' It's a " what.''

12:00.553 --> 12:02.578
Camille is a hurricane.

12:29.448 --> 12:33.316
<i>I don't remember anything</i>
<i>about Hurricane Camille, Al. What happened?</i>

12:33.385 --> 12:35.319
It was a killer storm, Sam.

12:35.387 --> 12:38.754
There were winds
up to 1 90 miles an hour.

12:38.824 --> 12:41.122
More than 360 people were killed.

12:41.193 --> 12:44.253
I remember the head of
the National Hurricane Center...

12:44.330 --> 12:49.267
said that this was the greatest storm
of any kind ever to affect this nation.

12:49.335 --> 12:53.772
And we're in its path.
No, we're a little off
to the side, thank God.

12:53.839 --> 12:55.966
It's still gonna be
a big deal here though.

12:56.041 --> 12:58.737
How much time do we have?
Well, no. No, I mean-

12:58.811 --> 13:00.802
I mean, what-what time
did the storm hit?

13:02.848 --> 13:08.047
<i>Well, at 1 0: 1 5, all the power lines,</i>
<i>all the telephone lines go down.</i>

13:08.120 --> 13:11.556
At 1 0:30, a three-story high
wall of water...

13:11.624 --> 13:15.219
is gonna come over the seawall
and flatten everything in its path.

13:15.294 --> 13:18.889
But not here.
No. No, we're fine here.

13:18.964 --> 13:21.296
Well, then where
does she get killed?

13:21.367 --> 13:24.200
<i>[ Ziggy Beeping ]</i>
She goes back to save
that hurricane party, doesn't she?

13:24.270 --> 13:29.298
No, actually you d- Uh, Arch-
You, Archie, did evacuate some people
from the hurricane party...

13:29.375 --> 13:33.709
just before the wall of water came
and leveled the entire apartment building.

13:33.779 --> 13:36.577
You were a big hero.
You saved 1 2 people's lives.

13:36.649 --> 13:41.245
But unfortunately, Cissy was killed
across town while you were at the beach.

13:41.320 --> 13:45.518
Some object came smashing
through the window of her house,
hit her on the head, killed her.

13:45.591 --> 13:47.684
<i>[ Rattling ]</i>

13:49.728 --> 13:53.687
<i>[ Continues ]</i>

13:53.766 --> 13:58.965
That's the shingles.
The wind must be flickin' 'em
off the roof like potato chips.

13:59.038 --> 14:01.268
Why did she go back
to her house?

14:01.340 --> 14:04.798
Ziggy hasn't got a clue about that.
But I can tell you this.

14:04.877 --> 14:08.278
The coroner's report
fixed the time of her death at 1 0:30,

14:08.347 --> 14:12.010
because she was wearing
a wristwatch that got smashed
and that was the time on the watch.

14:12.084 --> 14:16.282
She must've gone back to rescue
somethin' from the storm, right?
Well, then you better tell her to forget it.

14:16.355 --> 14:19.222
If it was that important,
she's not gonna forget about it.

14:19.291 --> 14:22.283
No, I-I gotta get her to go back
and do it earlier.

14:22.361 --> 14:27.128
Oh, my. If we get up
any earlier to do it,

14:27.199 --> 14:29.258
we might as well
not go to sleep.

14:29.335 --> 14:32.532
[ Chuckles ]
Which might not be
a bad idea after all.

14:33.772 --> 14:37.003
What I-What I was thinkin'
was that, uh-

14:37.076 --> 14:39.442
Since we're gonna be
so busy today, you know,

14:39.511 --> 14:42.002
evacuating people
and-and doin' all kinds of work,

14:42.081 --> 14:47.018
that if there's anything at your house
that you need, we should-
we should go back and get it now.

14:47.086 --> 14:50.283
Oh, that's slick, Sam.
Okay. Uh-

14:50.356 --> 14:53.723
<i>[ Ziggy Beeping ]</i>
First I'll have to think
of something to get.

14:53.792 --> 14:56.727
Okay. Well-well,
you do that, all right?

14:59.598 --> 15:02.590
I'm sorry, Sam.
She still gets killed.

15:02.668 --> 15:06.365
So you better stick with her
until she's back here, safe and sound.

15:06.438 --> 15:12.240
I'm gonna go back and see if
I can find out some way to figure out
what it is she went back for.

15:14.313 --> 15:16.304
Now you stick with her.

15:21.153 --> 15:23.951
<i>[ Pounds Fist ]</i>

15:24.023 --> 15:26.992
<i>[ Barking ]</i>

15:27.059 --> 15:32.554
[ Sighs ]
Archie, I know. I know.
I said I was goin', but-

15:32.631 --> 15:38.365
Well, it's just... seein' you again
made me think-

15:38.437 --> 15:42.533
I mean, what I want to say is,

15:42.608 --> 15:47.011
maybe you and I could go
to dinner some night, you know?

15:49.214 --> 15:51.842
Oh, Lisa.
I- I don't know, um-

15:51.917 --> 15:53.851
You're right. You're right.

15:53.919 --> 15:58.686
I'm sorry, you know,
a-about things.

15:58.757 --> 16:04.696
It's just you-
You wouldn't answer my phone calls,
and I-I called you at the station, and-

16:06.498 --> 16:11.265
I- I keep wonderin'... what if-

16:12.905 --> 16:14.839
W-
What?

16:14.907 --> 16:20.368
[ Sighs ]
What if... we'd stayed together?

16:20.446 --> 16:22.380
What if I'd never met Cissy?

16:26.385 --> 16:31.618
But I did, and...
I can't change that.

16:33.692 --> 16:36.217
[ Sighs ]
Some things you can change,

16:36.295 --> 16:40.231
and then there are some things
that... you can't.

16:42.768 --> 16:48.468
I know. I just... thought-

16:48.540 --> 16:51.134
I seem to have bad luck with men,

16:51.210 --> 16:54.611
just like my mom.

16:54.680 --> 16:58.013
All the ones I like leave,

16:58.083 --> 17:01.610
and I- I just thought-

17:03.455 --> 17:07.221
[ Crying ]
I can't eat.
I just think about you and-

17:07.291 --> 17:10.693
My daddy wouldn't even
stay with my mom, and-

17:10.762 --> 17:14.324
<i>[ Wind Whistling ]</i>

17:14.400 --> 17:17.425
Wow. The wind is really pickin' up.

17:17.502 --> 17:20.267
Yeah. Yeah, it is.

17:22.674 --> 17:24.608
You look good.

17:25.611 --> 17:27.442
So do you.

17:32.117 --> 17:34.642
What's his name?

17:34.720 --> 17:37.484
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>Oh, uh, Boface.</i>

17:37.556 --> 17:39.854
Hmm. He's pretty.

17:42.795 --> 17:45.025
Well-

17:46.765 --> 17:49.063
If you ever-

17:49.134 --> 17:51.602
You know-

17:51.670 --> 17:53.729
Yeah. Yeah, I know.

17:57.976 --> 17:59.739
You gonna be okay?
Yeah.

18:00.879 --> 18:03.211
Sure.
<i>Are you sure you don't want</i>
<i>to stay with us?</i>

18:03.282 --> 18:05.682
No.

18:05.751 --> 18:07.912
Bye.

18:11.290 --> 18:14.418
<i>[ Wind Chimes Ringing ]</i>

18:22.501 --> 18:24.435
<i>[ Car Door Closes ]</i>

18:28.507 --> 18:33.206
<i>[ Sam Narrating ] I couldn't help but wonder</i>
<i>if maybe I shouldn't have tried harder</i>
<i>to make Lisa stay.</i>

18:33.278 --> 18:39.239
<i>She seemed so lost and confused,</i>
<i>but at the same time oddly determined.</i>

18:39.318 --> 18:44.278
<i>Whatever Lisa felt for Archie</i>
<i>was too strong to let it rest,</i>
<i>and not even a hurricane could stop her.</i>

18:44.356 --> 18:46.290
[ Whimpers ]

18:56.735 --> 18:58.669
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Hello. Anybody home?</i>

18:58.737 --> 19:02.036
[ Woman ]
Hi, Archie. Come on, Daddy.
You're lettin' the storm in!

19:02.107 --> 19:04.371
Don't worry about me.
I'll be there. I'll be there.

19:04.443 --> 19:07.606
[ Sam ]
Need some help?
You could giveJoe a hand.

19:07.679 --> 19:11.479
Somebody forgot to turn off
the weather outside.

19:11.550 --> 19:13.745
Where's the cake?
Is this Joe's house?

19:13.819 --> 19:16.379
[ Woman ]
We told 'em we were going
toJoe's house for a party.

19:16.455 --> 19:18.855
It's the only way we could get 'em
to leave their place.

19:18.924 --> 19:21.256
Oh, you are real strong!
Today is their 61 st anniversary.

19:21.326 --> 19:23.260
Thank you, boys.

19:23.328 --> 19:27.321
You know, if you could make
the earth spin the other way,
you could unwind a hurricane.

19:27.399 --> 19:31.631
- [ Laughs ]
- Oh. Is he your husband?

19:31.703 --> 19:34.900
Uh, no. Not yet.
Well, you got
a mighty cute figure on you.

19:34.973 --> 19:36.907
You oughta make him
marry you.

19:36.975 --> 19:39.068
Hey, what do you think
about that?

19:39.144 --> 19:42.341
You oughta snatch him up
before some other gal does.
Hey, this ain'tJoe's place.

19:42.414 --> 19:45.440
What're we doin' here?
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>There's a hurricane comin'.</i>

19:45.517 --> 19:47.451
We can't stay here then.
We only knew each other-

19:47.519 --> 19:50.613
I gotta go back home
and hold the house down.
two weeks before we got married.

19:50.689 --> 19:54.648
That was before the war.
Otherwise, we might come home
and find we got a new address.

19:54.726 --> 19:57.126
D! Get me some water!
You can't be gettin'-

19:57.196 --> 19:59.130
Here we go now. Let's go.
Where are we goin'?

19:59.198 --> 20:01.189
You know, if we was smart-
Where's my hat?

20:01.266 --> 20:04.963
we'd figure out some way
to harness the power from a hurricane.
It's on your head. There you go.

20:05.037 --> 20:08.006
Let nature do the work.
[ Man ]
There's a hurricane comin'.

20:09.007 --> 20:12.340
That's why we invited
everybody over for the party.
That way you wouldn't have to leave.

20:12.411 --> 20:14.379
Party? What kind of party?
What kind of party?

20:14.446 --> 20:18.041
It's your anniversary party!
We've lots of cake
and ice cream.

20:18.116 --> 20:21.051
You gonna be there?
Oh, I wouldn't miss it
for the world.

20:21.119 --> 20:23.713
What's everybody screamin' for?

20:23.789 --> 20:26.883
Is it my birthday?

20:26.959 --> 20:31.293
[ Laughs ]
You can just put me right over there,
next to my sweetheart.

20:31.363 --> 20:34.628
Fetch some sodas from the cooler,
would you, please?
Okay.

20:34.700 --> 20:37.294
You know, I don't like you
wearin' that cold, wet-

20:37.369 --> 20:39.564
<i>I'm all right.</i>
<i>Don't be so picayunish, Mama.</i>

20:39.638 --> 20:41.731
<i>Well, I'm not picayunish.</i>
<i>Well, stop harpin'at me.</i>

20:41.807 --> 20:44.799
<i>[ Cissy ]</i>
<i>Can you believe that?</i>
<i>They got married after only two weeks.</i>

20:44.876 --> 20:47.902
Yeah.
Do you marry someone
after only a couple weeks?

20:49.915 --> 20:53.942
If it was the right someone,
I'd marry 'em after a couple of hours.

21:13.538 --> 21:15.472
[ Coughs ]

21:18.176 --> 21:21.475
[ Coughing ]

21:22.781 --> 21:26.410
[ Sighs ]
Nice.

21:29.621 --> 21:31.782
Nice? I'll bet it was nice.

21:31.857 --> 21:35.884
You should see a doctor
about that cough.
What cough?

21:35.961 --> 21:37.952
What do you got for me, Al?

21:38.030 --> 21:40.828
Well, I hate to interrupt
your hanky-panky here-
What do you got, Al?

21:40.899 --> 21:42.867
but Ziggy's come up
with a new wrinkle.

21:42.934 --> 21:46.961
It seems that one of the people here
is oneJoe... Deever.

21:47.039 --> 21:49.166
Yeah, yeah.
He just got here a little while ago.

21:49.241 --> 21:52.301
He came with his grandparents, his wife
and two kids. What about him?
Uh-uh.

21:52.377 --> 21:56.507
Uh-uh what, Al?
He came with his sister
and <i>her</i> two kids.

21:56.581 --> 21:59.141
Okay, he came with his sister
and her two kids. So what?

21:59.217 --> 22:04.416
So this is the kind of guy they're gonna
be writing box-office smashes about
20 years from now.

22:04.489 --> 22:07.151
<i>He's one of Cissy's ex-boyfriends.</i>

22:07.225 --> 22:12.492
He's got a hot temper,
he's a violent type, and he's insanely jealous.

22:12.564 --> 22:18.196
And according to Ziggy, Cissy is last seen
leaving Unabelle's... with him.

22:25.277 --> 22:28.110
Where's Cissy?
She and Joe just left.

22:52.404 --> 22:54.929
Cissy, what-Joe?

22:55.006 --> 22:57.440
What were you guys
doin' out there? I-

22:57.509 --> 23:00.410
Archie, are you okay?
Here. Let me get the door.

23:00.479 --> 23:02.413
Yeah, I'm fine, uh-

23:04.416 --> 23:07.044
I- I was just comin' out
to look for you.

23:07.119 --> 23:10.714
<i>[ Cissy ]</i>
<i>Well, here we are.</i>
Well, thanks. This is the last of it.

23:10.789 --> 23:15.624
Didn't have time to load up much else.
Joe, why don't you go put that
over in the bait shop?

23:17.362 --> 23:19.330
<i>[ Portal Opens ]</i>

23:21.199 --> 23:24.134
[ Cissy Laughing ]
Sam, I don't get it.
Nothing's changed.

23:24.202 --> 23:28.468
He's still the last one to see her.
She still gets killed.
[ Sighs ]

23:30.342 --> 23:32.572
- Cissy?
- Yeah?

23:34.546 --> 23:37.174
You better get this jacket off,
huh? Come on.
[ Laughs ]

23:37.249 --> 23:40.582
Thank you.
Yeah. Listen, um-

23:40.652 --> 23:44.679
Are you-Are you sure you got
all your stuff... from your house?

23:44.756 --> 23:48.351
[ Exhales ]
Archie, what's the matter with you?

23:48.427 --> 23:51.328
You've been actin' strange
all afternoon.

23:51.396 --> 23:54.263
Is it because
you saw her again today?

23:54.332 --> 23:56.197
<i>No.</i>
Her?

23:56.268 --> 23:59.533
No. No, no.
<i>Who, her? You mean there's</i>
<i>another woman involved in this?</i>

23:59.604 --> 24:01.162
<i>That has nothing</i>-
Why didn't you tell me?

24:03.742 --> 24:05.710
Who is she?

24:05.777 --> 24:09.042
Lisa came back here...

24:09.114 --> 24:13.016
a while ago,just beforeJoe
and his family arrived.

24:13.084 --> 24:17.646
- What'd she want?
- Well, she wanted
to make contact, I guess.

24:17.722 --> 24:19.656
Honey, I know you're a nice guy,

24:19.724 --> 24:24.218
but y-you just can't go around
encouraging her.
<i>I wasn't encouraging her.</i>

24:24.296 --> 24:26.526
Don't worry.
He's the original Boy Scout.

24:26.598 --> 24:29.362
<i>You know what I mean.</i>

24:29.434 --> 24:33.427
Look, Lisa's hurt because
you guys broke up, and she's lonely,

24:33.505 --> 24:36.531
and-and she doesn't wanna let
a good thing get away.

24:39.611 --> 24:41.670
And neither do I.

24:42.981 --> 24:47.543
Next to Boface,
you're the male I love most.

24:49.654 --> 24:51.815
How do you feel about holograms?

24:51.890 --> 24:54.723
<i>So that puts me pretty near</i>
<i>the top then, right?</i>

24:54.793 --> 24:56.727
Absolutely.

24:56.795 --> 25:01.391
<i>So then... it's pretty much over</i>
<i>between you and Joe, right?</i>

25:01.466 --> 25:03.400
[ Sighs ]
What's that supposed to mean?

25:03.468 --> 25:05.402
She's defensive, Sam.

25:05.470 --> 25:10.669
I just... wanna make sure that...
it's over, right?

25:10.742 --> 25:15.270
How many times
do I have to tell you?
That is ancient history.

25:15.347 --> 25:17.679
Yeah, but is it ancient history
with him?

25:19.618 --> 25:22.485
Look, Ar-Archie, are you-
Are you afraid he's gonna do something?

25:22.554 --> 25:26.513
No, no.
<i>That is exactly</i>
<i>what we're afraid of. Yes.!</i>

25:26.591 --> 25:31.187
Well, I-I'm just a little worried
that he might want to
take something out on you.

25:31.263 --> 25:33.925
I know he's got a temper.

25:33.999 --> 25:37.867
But we grew up together.
He'd never hurt me.

25:37.936 --> 25:41.201
He never even touched me
when we were goin' out together.

25:41.273 --> 25:43.707
That shoots that theory to hell.
If it's true.

25:43.775 --> 25:45.766
Course it's true.

25:45.844 --> 25:48.335
You're just-

25:48.413 --> 25:50.779
What was that word I read?

25:50.849 --> 25:54.615
Projectin' your fears.
It's just not gonna happen.

25:54.686 --> 25:57.484
Well, something certainly is.

25:57.556 --> 26:01.117
Projecting my fears?
You sound like a psychologist.
[ Laughs ]

26:02.561 --> 26:06.361
Well, that's me- Doc Cis.

26:06.431 --> 26:10.663
Oh, ex-boyfriends, current boyfriends,
ex-girlfriends- I can help 'em all.

26:10.735 --> 26:12.999
When you've been a nurse
as long as I have,

26:13.071 --> 26:18.805
you-you start to realize
that a... lot of people's problems
aren't physical.

26:22.080 --> 26:24.446
- Did you ever think about
becoming a psychologist?
- Me?

26:24.516 --> 26:25.847
Yeah.
No.

26:25.917 --> 26:29.978
When I was in nursing school,
I-I used to dream about being a doctor,

26:30.055 --> 26:33.650
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>
but, uh, now it's too late.

26:33.725 --> 26:37.388
No, it's- It's never too late,
not if you want something bad enough.

26:37.462 --> 26:41.796
Sam, psychologist, seismologist.
She's not even gonna have a future
unless you figure out-

26:41.866 --> 26:43.834
Archie, phone.
what's gonna happen to... her.

26:43.902 --> 26:46.462
Okay. Thanks.
It's never too late.

26:53.545 --> 26:57.379
Hello. Yeah, this is Archie.

26:58.850 --> 27:00.841
Yeah, Sheriff.

27:03.288 --> 27:08.658
- Heck of a night.
- [ Sighs ]
Yes, it is.

27:08.727 --> 27:11.924
Reminds me of Audrey
back in '57. Remember?
[ Chuckles ]

27:11.997 --> 27:17.833
When we stood up on the seawall
or when we climbed up into the trees?
Trees.

27:19.170 --> 27:21.536
It's just like we were
seven years old again.

27:21.606 --> 27:24.837
Swayin' in the wind,
back and forth,

27:26.111 --> 27:30.275
hangin' on for all we were worth
40 feet above the ground.

27:30.348 --> 27:32.407
Our parents went crazy
lookin' for us.

27:32.484 --> 27:35.180
And us havin'
the times of our lives.
[ Chuckles ]

27:36.221 --> 27:38.212
He treatin' you right?

27:40.625 --> 27:42.559
[ Sighs ]
Joe.

27:45.230 --> 27:47.164
Just lookin' out for you is all.

27:47.232 --> 27:49.598
I appreciate that.

27:49.668 --> 27:52.102
But you want me to butt out.

27:52.170 --> 27:56.197
I want you to be
the friend you've always been.

27:56.274 --> 27:59.243
[ Scoffs, Laughs ]

27:59.310 --> 28:02.711
You know what the three worst words
in the English language are?

28:03.982 --> 28:06.576
"Let's be friends.''

28:10.822 --> 28:13.017
Joe, come on.

28:13.091 --> 28:16.254
It's just hard watchin' you
with him, that's all.

28:17.662 --> 28:23.032
Particularly since we are-
since we <i>were</i> so close.

28:23.101 --> 28:26.559
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>No, they're havin'a hurricane party</i>-
Um-

28:28.506 --> 28:30.531
- Cissy, hold on.
- Uh, Sam.

28:30.608 --> 28:33.577
Yeah?
Sam. S-Wait. Look.

28:33.645 --> 28:37.137
<i>[Joe ]</i>
<i>Just hear me out. Hear me out.</i>
<i>I'm not gonna bite you.</i>

28:37.215 --> 28:40.616
<i>Archie, what</i>- <i>What is it?</i>

28:40.685 --> 28:42.744
You all right?
Yeah.

28:42.821 --> 28:46.313
<i>Tell this nozzle to take a hike.</i>

28:46.391 --> 28:48.382
We, uh-

28:48.460 --> 28:50.724
We gotta go back
to the hurricane party.

28:52.063 --> 28:53.997
Don't let me stop you.

28:58.536 --> 29:00.629
[ Chattering ]

29:00.705 --> 29:04.698
You looked like
you were gonna-
I know. I know. I just-

29:04.776 --> 29:07.006
I just thought-
<i>[ Thumping ]</i>

29:07.078 --> 29:09.012
I don't believe you did that.

29:09.080 --> 29:12.049
My knight in shinin'... khaki-

29:12.117 --> 29:14.608
[ Chuckles ]
chargin' to the rescue.

29:16.321 --> 29:18.812
Look, I'm sorry.

29:18.890 --> 29:21.484
I-I just-
I overreacted a little bit. I, uh-

29:21.559 --> 29:25.928
<i>You know, sometimes, uh, knights</i>
<i>would get rewards from the damsel...</i>

29:25.997 --> 29:29.592
<i>when they helped them in a</i>-
I like seeing you jealous.

29:29.667 --> 29:31.498
I think you're gonna get a reward.

29:31.569 --> 29:33.662
It's kind of sweet.

29:34.806 --> 29:38.139
<i>Sweet,yeah.</i>

29:39.744 --> 29:43.111
Yeah, but you know, Sam,
I don't think in the-
in the closet there, uh-

29:44.282 --> 29:46.216
Sam?

29:47.786 --> 29:49.720
Oh.

29:49.788 --> 29:52.279
You gotta make it a king.
You gotta put the king-

29:52.357 --> 29:54.018
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Sit down.</i>

29:57.362 --> 30:00.297
Here you go.
[ Whimpers ]

30:02.600 --> 30:04.966
Come on. Come on.

30:07.939 --> 30:09.964
Isn't it gonna get
a little hot in there?

30:10.041 --> 30:13.204
[ Cissy Moans ]

30:13.278 --> 30:16.475
Oh, we should-
We should go now-

30:16.548 --> 30:19.073
[ Sam ]
Yeah.

30:19.150 --> 30:21.675
<i>All right, Sam. I'll see you later.</i>

30:21.753 --> 30:24.722
Don't forget the... hurricane.

30:24.789 --> 30:29.783
<i>I'll, uh, meet you at the hurricane party.</i>
<i>I'm goin'to check on them now.</i>

30:29.861 --> 30:31.795
<i>Uh, bye.</i>

30:33.064 --> 30:35.123
[ Sighs ]

30:37.769 --> 30:40.067
[ Both Panting ]

30:44.142 --> 30:46.372
<i>Boface?</i>

30:49.781 --> 30:52.944
Boface?
<i>Joe took him to the kitchen</i>
<i>for some water.</i>

30:53.017 --> 30:55.417
He was scratchin' to go out
so I let him.

30:58.289 --> 31:02.123
<i>Wait, wait, wait.</i>
<i>Where-Where you goin'?</i>
Home. That's where Boface is headed.

31:02.193 --> 31:04.127
Come on, Sam.
You better hurry up.
I know!

31:04.195 --> 31:06.595
I-I know where he's headed.
I'll go get him.
I'll get him.

31:06.664 --> 31:08.757
No!
No!

31:08.833 --> 31:12.769
Look, I'll go get Boface and I'll go
over to the apartments, all right?
But you can't do both.

31:12.837 --> 31:15.772
It's too dangerous for everybody
to be runnin' around outside
right now.

31:15.840 --> 31:19.537
You stay here where it's safe,
and I'll come back as soon as I can.
You won't even know I'm gone.

31:19.611 --> 31:21.602
Want me to go with you?
<i>No, thank you.</i>

31:23.715 --> 31:25.649
I'll see you.
You be careful!

31:25.717 --> 31:27.651
[ Sam ]
Get it closed.

31:27.719 --> 31:30.984
What's everybody
slammin' doors for?

31:42.033 --> 31:45.400
<i>[ Sam Narrating ]</i>
<i>I didn't know whyJoe</i>
<i>let Boface out into the storm,</i>

31:45.470 --> 31:48.598
<i>unless it was to lure</i>
<i>Cissy back to her house.</i>

31:48.673 --> 31:51.141
<i>But I figured that as long</i>
<i>as I went there instead ofher,</i>

31:51.209 --> 31:54.144
<i>Cissy would remain alive,</i>
<i>and that I would leap out ofhere...</i>

31:54.212 --> 31:56.203
<i>as soon as I returned with Boface.</i>

31:56.281 --> 31:59.546
<i>That is, assuming I survived the storm.</i>

32:07.692 --> 32:11.253
<i>[ Wind Whistling ]</i>
Boface!

32:12.563 --> 32:15.794
- [ Electricity Crackling ]
- Boface!

32:27.045 --> 32:29.445
Boface. Here, boy!

32:33.351 --> 32:37.048
Here, boy! Boface!

32:39.691 --> 32:43.092
That-a-boy. There you go.

32:44.529 --> 32:47.726
Easy, Boface, easy.
[ Whining ]

32:47.799 --> 32:50.393
Come on. That's it.

32:51.602 --> 32:55.868
Ah- Come on.
Come on, Boface.

32:55.940 --> 32:59.000
[ Barks ]
We're almost there.

32:59.077 --> 33:02.774
Ah. Come on. Come on.

33:02.847 --> 33:05.338
Come on, Boface.

33:07.018 --> 33:10.283
Yeah. Easy, Boface.
Easy, easy.

33:10.355 --> 33:13.882
[ Whining ]

33:13.958 --> 33:17.257
[ Car Door Closes ]
Easy, Bo. Easy, Bo.

33:17.328 --> 33:21.264
How's it goin', Sam? Boy, it's
really blowin' out here, isn't it?

33:21.332 --> 33:23.266
Oh, I see you got the dog.
That's good.

33:23.334 --> 33:25.268
[ Beeping ]

33:25.336 --> 33:27.270
Uh-oh!
What?

33:27.338 --> 33:29.272
I don't know.
You must've changed history, Sam.

33:29.340 --> 33:32.935
Cissy still dies, but this time
it happens back at Unabelle's!

33:42.653 --> 33:46.555
<i>[ Wind Whistling ]</i>

33:49.360 --> 33:51.760
<i>How does Cissy get killed</i>
<i>back at Unabelle's?</i>

33:51.829 --> 33:54.992
[ Beeping ]
A hunk of debris
bonks her on the head.

33:55.066 --> 33:58.263
- Al, let's-
- [ Electricity Crackling ]

34:00.838 --> 34:05.275
Uh-oh. It's 1 0:1 5, Sam.
All the power in Jackson's Point
just went off.

34:05.343 --> 34:08.005
That means that in 1 5 minutes,
that giant wall of water...

34:08.079 --> 34:11.242
is gonna come over the seawall
and flatten everything in its path!

34:11.315 --> 34:16.275
If I go back and save Cissy, does Archie
have enough time to go to the apartments
and save those people?

34:16.353 --> 34:18.583
Uh, that's a negative, Sam.

34:18.656 --> 34:22.888
No, if you save Cissy
at Unabelle's and leap out,
Ziggy says there's no way in hell...

34:22.960 --> 34:26.760
that the real Archie
could get back to those apartments
to save those people from the wave!

34:26.831 --> 34:28.924
Then what the hell
am I doin' here?
I don't know.

34:29.000 --> 34:32.993
Uh, maybe it's tryin' to fix somethin'
that the real Archie didn't do or somethin'.
I don't know!

34:35.540 --> 34:38.839
This is 28 to base, over!

34:38.909 --> 34:42.505
<i>[ Man On Police Radio ]</i>
<i>Archie, where the hell are you?</i>
<i>You should've been 1 0-39 an hour ago.</i>

34:42.580 --> 34:45.014
Uh, that means
back at the station.

34:45.083 --> 34:48.449
Look, it doesn't matter.
I need you to send a car
over to Gulf View Apartments...

34:48.518 --> 34:50.612
to get those people
out of that hurricane party.

34:50.688 --> 34:54.283
Over.
<i>Everybody's up at the other end</i>
<i>of the county already, Archie.</i>

34:54.358 --> 34:58.089
<i>And you better get your</i>
<i>butt up there, too. 1 0-4?</i>
You can't do both, man. You can't.

34:59.764 --> 35:02.927
All right, listen to me.
I need you to get in touch
with my girlfriend, Cissy Davis.

35:03.000 --> 35:04.934
She's at Unabelle's Bait and Rest.

35:05.002 --> 35:10.133
Tell her to stay inside.
I know it sounds crazy.
Just do it, all right? Over.

35:10.208 --> 35:13.700
<i>Arch, we got phone lines down all over.</i>
<i>I don't know if we can do it. 1 0-4?</i>

35:13.778 --> 35:17.714
Then send somebody!
<i>Everybody's out.</i>
<i>You're the only one even close.</i>

35:17.782 --> 35:18.806
<i>Where you headed? 1 0-4.</i>

35:23.121 --> 35:27.319
Gulf View Apartments.
1 0-4. Over and out.
<i>[ Mike Settles In Base ]</i>

35:27.391 --> 35:33.091
All right, Al. What does Ziggy say
is the closest safe place
to the apartments?

35:33.164 --> 35:38.192
Uh, well, some people
would say that's the Gulfport Bank.
It's... two blocks away.

35:38.269 --> 35:40.794
All right.
I'm going to the apartments.

35:40.872 --> 35:43.306
You go find Cissy, all right?
Stay with her.

35:43.374 --> 35:46.070
Okay. I'll stay with Cissy.
Good luck, Sam.

35:46.144 --> 35:48.635
Thanks.
Come on, Boface.

35:48.713 --> 35:50.578
[ Whining, Barks ]

35:50.648 --> 35:52.843
All right? All right, let's go.

35:52.917 --> 35:56.080
[ Electricity Crackling ]

36:03.060 --> 36:05.392
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>Open up. Open the door.</i>

36:05.463 --> 36:07.397
Hold your horses. I'm comin'.

36:10.468 --> 36:13.460
<i>All right. Everybody out.!</i>
<i>Let's go.!</i>

36:13.538 --> 36:15.699
Get outta here right now!
<i>Look, I told you before.</i>

36:15.773 --> 36:17.968
I don't have time to discuss it!
Get the hell out of here!

36:18.042 --> 36:20.203
If you don't, you're all
gonna be killed in a few minutes!

36:20.278 --> 36:22.940
Now, Sheriff, simmer down.
Nobody's goin' nowhere.

36:23.014 --> 36:25.141
[ Screaming ]
Get the hell out of here. I mean it!

36:25.216 --> 36:27.309
Hey!
Go to the Gulfport Bank.
It's two blocks from here.

36:27.385 --> 36:30.377
Don't stop for anything!
This whole area's gonna be flooded
in eight minutes!

36:30.454 --> 36:31.819
Hey!
What?

36:31.889 --> 36:35.347
You're one mean son of a bitch.
Yeah. Well, I just saved your life.
Now get the hell out of here.

36:35.426 --> 36:37.417
All right. Okay.
Go on!

36:47.305 --> 36:49.739
[ Chattering ]
[ Shutters Banging ]

36:49.807 --> 36:51.741
Come on, Sam.

36:53.578 --> 36:55.739
Come on. Hurry up!

37:01.819 --> 37:03.912
[ Beeping ]
<i>[ Banging ]</i>

37:03.988 --> 37:06.286
- [ Glass Breaking ]
- [ Screams ]

37:06.357 --> 37:09.053
All right!
Everybody up!

37:09.126 --> 37:13.586
What's the ruckus about?
[ All Shouting ]

37:17.335 --> 37:19.269
Away from the windows!
Come on!

37:19.337 --> 37:21.305
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>

37:25.109 --> 37:27.043
Archie?

37:28.312 --> 37:30.246
Lisa!

37:30.314 --> 37:34.410
The causeway to Clanton was washed out,
and... I didn't know where else to go.

37:34.485 --> 37:36.817
Did you see Archie out there?
[ Ziggy Beeping ]

37:36.887 --> 37:38.855
No. No, I didn't.

37:38.923 --> 37:43.951
Now wait a second.
That causeway wasn't washed out.

37:52.903 --> 37:57.033
Let's get to the back
where it's safe.
You know, I'd like some coffee.

37:57.108 --> 38:01.408
[ Sighs ]
Okay, I-I'll get you a towel
and some coffee.

38:01.479 --> 38:03.413
<i>You wait right there.</i>

38:10.788 --> 38:12.722
<i>[ Ziggy Beeping ]</i>

38:18.562 --> 38:21.497
<i>[ Al ]</i>
<i>I got a funny feeling about this.</i>

38:24.235 --> 38:27.329
Hmm, who is she?
Come on, Ziggy.

38:27.405 --> 38:31.068
<i>Give me</i>- <i>Uh-oh.</i>
<i>Uh-oh, Ziggy.</i>

38:31.142 --> 38:33.167
<i>Give me some information here.</i>
<i>[ Cissy ]</i>
<i>Lisa?</i>

38:34.245 --> 38:37.840
<i>Archie used to take me fishin'</i>
<i>all the time.</i>

38:37.915 --> 38:39.849
How 'bout you?

38:39.917 --> 38:44.718
Uh, no. Uh, we haven't
gotten around to that yet.

38:50.928 --> 38:53.488
You know,

38:55.333 --> 38:58.029
everything was fine
until you came along,

39:03.274 --> 39:06.107
until you stole Archie.

39:06.177 --> 39:11.080
Lisa, I didn't steal Archie.
He-He made up his own mind.

39:12.750 --> 39:15.048
No, he didn't.

39:15.119 --> 39:17.713
<i>Oh, I don't like</i>
<i>the looks of this.</i>

39:17.788 --> 39:20.552
Cissy, you better get out of here.
Get out of here! Get out. Get out!

39:23.494 --> 39:25.860
Sam, you gotta hurry!

39:25.930 --> 39:29.297
Lisa's back at Unabelle's
and she's got a knife!
What?

39:29.367 --> 39:31.631
Yeah! She's goin' after Cissy!

39:32.803 --> 39:36.204
- Lisa, come on.
Put the knife down.
- No.

39:36.273 --> 39:38.104
- Put it down.
- It's too late.

39:38.175 --> 39:40.643
[ Both Grunting ]

39:45.516 --> 39:47.780
[ Screaming ]

39:47.852 --> 39:51.583
- Stop!
- <i>[ Pottery Shatters ]</i>

39:58.129 --> 39:59.289
<i>[ Portal Opens ]</i>

39:59.363 --> 40:02.127
[ Both Shouting, Grunting ]

40:02.199 --> 40:06.260
[ Groans, Panting ]

40:07.304 --> 40:09.067
[ Gasping, Groaning ]

40:11.075 --> 40:13.100
<i>Cissy, get up. Get up.!</i>
<i>Get up.! Get up.!</i>

40:16.380 --> 40:21.181
[ Grunts ]
No. Let go of me!

40:22.186 --> 40:25.314
[ Sam ]
No! What are you doing?

40:25.389 --> 40:30.383
You said sometimes there are things
we can change, and sometimes
there are things we can't change.

40:30.461 --> 40:32.395
[ Sobbing ]
Well, I wanna change things.

40:32.463 --> 40:36.900
I want us back together.
You can't do that by killing Cissy.

40:36.967 --> 40:39.868
But then we'll be together.
[ Yelps ]

40:42.139 --> 40:44.073
Lisa!
I'm gonna kill her!

40:44.141 --> 40:46.939
No! Cissy.

40:47.011 --> 40:50.276
You all right?
Come on. Come on!
<i>[ Screams ]</i>

40:50.347 --> 40:53.282
<i>Sam, behind you.!</i>
[ Revolver Cocks ]

40:53.350 --> 40:55.875
<i>Lisa, put down the knife.</i>

40:55.953 --> 40:58.478
I love you. Can't you see?

40:58.556 --> 41:00.990
I do, but-
No, you don't!

41:01.058 --> 41:05.927
Everybody hates me.
Everybody leaves me,
but I'm not gonna let you!

41:05.996 --> 41:10.695
I'm gonna kill you, and you're gonna
have to kill me to stop you,
and then we'll be together!

41:10.768 --> 41:12.497
[ Grunting ]

41:12.570 --> 41:14.970
Shoot her, Sam. Shoot her!
[ Sobbing ]

41:16.273 --> 41:18.468
I love you!

41:21.879 --> 41:26.316
- Don't!
- [ Sobbing ]

41:32.456 --> 41:35.823
[ Sobbing Continues ]

41:38.762 --> 41:41.458
<i>[ Birds Squawking ]</i>

41:50.774 --> 41:52.799
[ Chattering ]

41:52.877 --> 41:54.902
Bye, everybody.
There you go.

41:54.979 --> 41:56.913
Bye.
Bye, y'all!

41:59.016 --> 42:00.950
Everybody's leaving except me.

42:01.018 --> 42:02.952
I don't know.
I don't understand it.

42:03.020 --> 42:05.386
You saved Cissy. You saved
the people at the hurricane party.

42:05.456 --> 42:07.583
You should have been out of here
a couple of hours ago.

42:07.658 --> 42:10.684
[ Sighs ]
What do you think's
gonna happen to Lisa?

42:11.729 --> 42:14.527
Lisa? Well, um-
Oh.

42:14.598 --> 42:17.089
I don't know. I think, um-
[ Beeping ]

42:17.167 --> 42:20.398
Well, I think with the right help,
she's probably gonna be-

42:22.139 --> 42:24.835
She'll probably be okay.
[ Beeping, Whining ]

42:24.909 --> 42:27.173
Don't look at me.

42:27.244 --> 42:29.678
Hmm.
That's on the nose, Sam. Yes.

42:29.747 --> 42:34.980
After a couple of years
of intensive therapy,
she turns out to be pretty much okay.

42:36.520 --> 42:41.184
Look, I'm not saying
that you would help <i>her.</i>

42:41.258 --> 42:46.195
I'm just saying that with the right training,
maybe you could help
a lot of people like her.

42:46.263 --> 42:49.596
[ Sighs ]
I mean, look. You're caring.
You're perceptive. You're smart.

42:49.667 --> 42:53.159
You've got every good trait
to be a psychologist.

42:53.237 --> 42:56.934
Oh, but then I'd have to
go back to school.
So what?

42:57.007 --> 43:00.465
I don't think I could face that.
It's kind of scary.

43:00.544 --> 43:03.479
[ Chuckles ]
What have you got to be scared of?

43:03.547 --> 43:07.847
You just lived through a hurricane
and you were almost killed in the middle of it.

43:07.918 --> 43:10.887
I had some help.
Well, yes, you did. That's true.

43:12.256 --> 43:14.190
But-
But what?

43:14.258 --> 43:18.285
Maybe if I had some more help,
I could get through school too.
Well.

43:18.362 --> 43:21.991
<i>That's what the sheriff department's</i>
<i>here for, ma'am.</i>

43:22.066 --> 43:25.524
[ Laughs ]
Thank goodness
I've got their number.

43:25.603 --> 43:27.537
[ Chuckles ]
<i>Ah, bingo.</i>

43:27.605 --> 43:33.510
Yep, she goes back to school, Sam,
and she becomes a psychotherapist.

43:33.577 --> 43:35.943
I'm just so glad we're together.

43:37.514 --> 43:39.448
Yeah.

43:41.952 --> 43:43.886
Me too.

43:54.498 --> 43:57.160
<i>[ Fire Crackling ]</i>

43:57.234 --> 43:59.964
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>And we shall dedicate our lives...</i>

44:00.037 --> 44:02.130
<i>to the preservation...</i>

44:02.206 --> 44:06.575
<i>of the purity of the white race.</i>

44:06.644 --> 44:11.604
<i>We fight to the death</i>
<i>to resurrect our country...</i>

44:11.682 --> 44:16.915
<i>from the fires of racial degradation.</i>

44:19.189 --> 44:22.750
And now,
by the powers vested in me...

44:22.826 --> 44:27.160
as a Royal Dragon of the Ku Klux Klan,

44:27.231 --> 44:31.258
I dub thee, fellow Klansman.

44:42.312 --> 44:44.246
Oh, boy.

